==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Confucianism
<hw>Con*fu"cian*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The political
morality taught by Confucius and his disciples, which forms the basis of
the Chinese jurisprudence and education. It can hardly be called a
religion, as it does not inculcate the worship of any god.</def>
<rj><au>S. W. Williams.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Confucianist</ent>⟦br⟧
